      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 125 (Thursday, July 20, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. RASKIN:H.R. 4802.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, Clause 18 (Necessary and ProperClause)The single subject of this legislation is:To prohibit employers from using non-disclosure agreements(NDAs) to silence victims of workplace misconduct.[Page H3890]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
